week.
   2. ``Scrooged,'' Paramount, $7.5 million, 1,262 screens, $5,947
per screen, $29.2 million, second week.
   3. ``Tequila Sunrise,'' Warner Bros., $6.3 million, 1,115
screens, $5,695 per screen, $6.3 million, one week.
   4. ``The Land Before Time,'' Universal, $3.5 million, 1,403
screens, $2,520 per screen, $23.09 million, three weeks.
   5. ``Oliver and Co.,'' Disney, $3.1 million, 952 screens, $3,257
per screen, $16.02 million, three weeks.
   6. ``Ernest Saves Christmas,'' Disney, $2.3 million, 1,640
screens, $1,457 per screen, $21.6 million, four weeks.
   7. ``Child's Play,'' United Artists, $2.2 million, 1,457 screens,
$1,559 per screen, $25.2 million, four weeks.
   8. ``Cocoon: The Return,'' 20th Century Fox, $2.1 million, 986
screens, $2,147 per screen, $10.6 million, two weeks.
   9. ``The Accused,'' Paramount, $725,273, 812 screens, $893 per
screen, $27.7 million, eight weeks.
   10. ``High Spirits,'' Tri-Star, $687,232, 821 screens, $837 per
screen, $7.3 million, three weeks.
