<HEAD>Woman Gets 30 Days in Jail In Animal Cruelty Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who baked her boyfriend's parrot
following an argument was sentenced to 30 days in the Los Angeles
County Jail and prohibited from owning a pet for three years.
   Superior Court Judge Bernard J. Kamins on Monday also was placed
Guadelupe Rodriguez to three years' probation, suspended 365 days of
the jail sentence and reduced the felony animal cruelty by torture
charge to a misdemeanor.
   Ms. Rodriguez, 26, had pleaded guilty to the felony in September.
   Ms. Rodriguez put the bird into a covered pot after her
boyfriend, 29-year-old Robert Carballo, stormed out following an
argument. She put the pot in the oven and set the temperature at 450
degrees.
   The bird was able to escape from the pot as the temperature rose,
and thrashed about in the oven until it died, according to
prosecutors.
