   ``After so many steps in the wrong direction, the INF Treaty is a
step in the right one.'' _ The Bulletin of the Atomic Scientists
citing the U.S.-Soviet Intermediate-range Nuclear Forces treaty as
the reason it turned back its symbolic doomsday clock to six minutes
before midnight, signaling its view that the superpowers have
stepped back from the brink of apocalypse.
