<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     12-06 0425</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0438</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Temperatures Plunge Below Freezing in Parts of New England,
Southeast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Temperatures plunged below freezing in northern New England and
in parts of the Southeast today and ocean winds spread rain through
the Pacific Northwest.
   Early morning readings were in the single digits and teens in
most of Vermont, New Hampshire and Maine, in contrast to milder 30s
and 40s in most other northern states.
   Temperatures dipped into the 20s in a few Southeast spots, with
Asheville, N.C., reporting 25 degrees at 2 a.m. EST and Augusta,
Ga., reporting 27 degrees.
   Rain along the Pacific Northwest coast was expected to turn to
freezing rain and snow in some inland areas. A snow advisory was in
effect for northeast Washington and a freezing rain advisory was
posted for the rest of the state's eastern part.
   Scattered rain doused parts of southern Texas and the east coast
of Florida, and dense fog advisories were posted for northwest Utah
and the central San Joaquin Valley in California.
   Skies were clear over most other regions.
   Today's forecast called for rain over the northern Pacific Coast,
turning to freezing rain in eastern Washington. Snow was forecast
for northwest Montana and northern Maine.
   Highs were predicted to be in the 20s in northern Maine and in
the 30s and 40s across the northern portion of the country from the
Pacific Northwest to the northern Rockies and Plains, the Great
Lakes, the northern Appalachians and New England. Readings were
expected to climb into the 70s in Southern California, the desert
Southwest and the coasts of Texas and Florida, while 50s and 60s
were forecast for the rest of the nation.
   At 2 a.m. EST, temperatures ranged from zero at Houlton, Maine,
to 68 degrees at Ontario and Van Nuys, Calif.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 38 fair; Boston 21 cloudy; Buffalo 40 windy;
Charleston, S.C. 32 fair; Cincinnati 34 fair; Cleveland 36 fair;
Detroit 32 fair; Miami 60 fair; New York 33 fair; Philadelphia 31
fair; Pittsburgh 36 fair; Portland, Maine 11 fair; Washington 33
fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 41 fair; Chicago 35 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth 45
partly cloudy; Denver 25 fair; Des Moines 31 fair; Indianapolis 33
fair; Kansas City 40 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 29 fair; Nashville
28 fair; New Orleans 40 foggy; St. Louis 44 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 30 fair; Las Vegas 45 fair; Los Angeles 59
fair; Phoenix 57 fair; Salt Lake City 28 foggy; San Diego 52 fair;
San Francisco 51 partly cloudy; Seattle 50 rain.
   _Canada: Montreal 23 cloudy; Toronto 34 hazy.
</TEXT>
