<HEAD>All Cruise Missiles to be Out of Belgium by Dec. 13</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 16 medium-range cruise missiles
based at Florennes air force base will be gone by Dec. 13, the
Defense Ministry said Tuesday.
   Defense Minister Guy Coeme and U.S. Ambassador Maynard W. Glitman
invited reporters to watch the removal of the last missile on
Belgian soil on that day.
   Under a 1979 NATO decision, 48 cruise missiles were to have been
deployed in Belgium, but the treaty signed a year ago by President
Reagan and Soviet leader Mikhail S. Gorbachev stopped the deployment
after only 16 had been based.
   Florennes is 40 miles south of Brussels.
