<DOCNO> AP881206-0116 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-06-88 1327EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--Make-A-Wish     12-06 0078</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Make-A-Wish,70</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Organization For Ill Children Gets $2 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A foundation that grants special wishes to
children with life-threatening illnesses has been given a $2 million
line of credit for local chapters that might be temporarily short of
funds.
   Hardee's Food Systems Inc. of Rocky Mount, N.C., announced the
funding Tuesday for the Make-A-Wish program. Local chapters must
repay the loan once they are able.
   Make-A-Wish, based in Phoenix, Ariz., was formed in 1983.
</TEXT>
