<FILEID>AP-NR-12-06-88 1326EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-ContinentalChairman     12-06 0207</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Continental Chairman,0215</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former TWA President Named Chairman of Continental</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   D. Joseph Corr, the former president of Trans
World Airlines, has been named chairman and chief executive officer
of Continental Airlines, the company announced Tuesday.
   Corr replaces Frank Lorenzo, chairman of Continental's parent
company, Texas Air Corp. Lorenzo will remain a director of the
Houston-based carrier.
   ``Joe Corr's record speaks for itself. He is a superb manager who
has improved the performance of several companies,'' Lorenzo said.
``He understands the airline business, and we are confident that he
will build on the progress that has been made at Continental.''
   Lorenzo also said that Corr's selection ``emphasizes Texas Air's
commitment to managing our airlines separately, and it will allow me
to devote all of my time to Texas Air activities.
   Texas Air also owns Miami-based Eastern Airlines.
   As president of TWA beginning in April 1986, Corr helped lead the
carrier from potential bankruptcy to record profitability,
Continental said in a statement announcing the appointment.
   He accomplished the same at ACF Industries, where profits
increased fourfold between 1983 and 1986, the statement said. Corr
served in various capacities at ACF from 1977 and 1988, including
president between 1984 and 1986 and vice chairman since 1986.
</TEXT>
