<1ST_LINE>r f AM-GoodyearCEO     12-06 0147</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Goodyear CEO,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Goodyear Names New CEO</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Goodyear Tire & Rubber Co. said Tuesday it has
elected its president Tom H. Barrett to be chief executive officer.
   Barrett, 58, replaces Robert E. Mercer, who will continue as
board chairman until March, when he reaches the company's mandatory
retirement age of 65 for elected officers.
   Barrett, who has been company president since 1982, will continue
in that position, Goodyear said.
   Goodyear said Barrett's election will help ensure an orderly
transition in top management.
   A native of Topeka, Kan., Barrett has been with Goodyear 35 years
and has been a company officer for 12 years, according to Goodyear.
   Mercer joined Goodyear in 1947 and has been an officer for the
company since 1976. He was elected president in 1978, chief
operating officer in 1980, vice chairman and CEO in 1982 and
chairman in 1983.

</TEXT>
</DOC>
