<1ST_LINE>u f AM-AndersenSuit     12-06 0219</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Andersen Suit,0226</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former Andersen Consultants Sue Over Competition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former consultants at Arthur Andersen & Co.
announced Tuesday they are suing the company, alleging that Andersen
is trying to damage a competing consulting firm they started.
   The lawsuit was announced by seven former employees, six of whom
left Andersen this year and started their own competing firm,
Information Consulting Group Inc., with the assistance of Saatchi &
Saatchi PLC of Britain.
   ``Andersen has embarked on a deliberate campaign to injure ICG,''
the group said in a statement. ``It has made false statements about
ICG and has threatened to sue employees, including secretaries, who
resign from Andersen and join ICG.''
   An Andersen spokesman who asked not to be identified said he had
not seen the lawsuit and could not comment directly on it.
   ``The Saatchi-backed ICG managing directors may be responding to
our success in expediting the information-gathering process in our
own suit against them,'' an Andersen statement said.
   Andersen has sued Saatchi and ICG, accusing them of trying to
force Andersen to sell at least part of its consulting business.
   The suit filed Tuesday by the former consultants charges that
Andersen owes them income, retirement benefits and their capital
contributions to Andersen. The group seeks a court-supervised
accounting to establish the exact amounts owed them.
</TEXT>
