<2ND_LINE>AM-Newspaper Union, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0297,0144</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Employees at The Hour Vote to Form Union</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: CORRECTS throughout to show that vote was to join union, sted
form one; DELETES final graf; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NORWALK, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Reporters and wire editors at The Hour of
Norwalk voted Tuesday to join the International Newspaper Guild.
   Reporters and wire editors voted 25-4 to form Local 3 of the
Guild.
   The vote came nearly a year after reporters at the Hour began
organizing efforts.
   ``We had to drag the company kicking and screaming into the
1980s,'' said Michael McIntire, a reporter and one of the union
organizers.
   Richard E. Curran, the newspaper's general manager, declined to
comment on the vote when contacted by telephone Tuesday night.
   Gregory Tarr, another organizer, said negotiations on a contract
are expected to begin later this month.
</TEXT>
